[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]Once you've cleared a tree (felled it and dug up the stump), nothing grows back in that spot. Great if you've laid out a graveyard or garden and don't want the vanilla re-spawn tick putting saplings through your careful layout.[/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][b]Permanent clearance[/b] — every tree you fully remove stays removed for as long as the mod is installed.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Works retroactively[/b] — trees already cleared in your save stay gone too.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]No effect on living trees[/b] — still-standing trees are untouched. The mod only suppresses the respawn on cleared tiles.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]No unlock required[/b] — install and the suppression starts immediately.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3]If you uninstall the mod, vanilla's respawn ticks will gradually repopulate cleared spots again over time.[/size]

[size=4][b]Other mods of mine you might like[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/60]I Build Where I Want[/url] — build anywhere you've cleared, not just in pre-defined zones.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/51]Auto-Loot Heavies[/url] — teleports the logs and timber to the nearest stockpile as you fell trees.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/70]Give Me Moar[/url] — multiplier on log/timber drops. Every tree becomes a bigger payout.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/54]Apple Trees Enhanced[/url] — only affects garden apple trees and berry bushes, not wild trees.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Configuration[/b][/size]

[size=3]If you installed the required [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack[/url] and this mod is configurable, press F1 in-game to open the config interface.[/size]

[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79][size=3]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack at Graveyard Keeper Nexus - Mods and community (nexusmods.com)[/size][/url]
[/list]
[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]

[size=3]Installation using Vortex is the recommended installation method. If you wish to install manually, extract the contents of the mod archive into:

[code]...&#92;steamapps&#92;common&#92;Graveyard Keeper&#92;BepInEx[/code][/size]

